olive oil
2 potato
1 bunch spring onion
½ cup water
20 g butter
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet sour cream
1 packet Soffritto Mix
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet pulled beef
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• While fries are baking, place grated Parmesan cheese in even circles (2 per person) on a second lined oven tray. Bake until golden and crisp at edges, 4-5 minutes.
• Remove Parmesan crisps from oven and set aside to cool.
• Meanwhile, thinly slice spring onion. Drain brine from pulled beef packet, then roughly chop beef.

TIP: Keep an eye on the Parmesan crisps as they can burn easily. They'll become crisp as they cool.

• When fries have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook soffritto mix until softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add pulled beef, All-American spice blend and the water and cook until fragrant, 2-3 minutes.
• Add the butter and stir until melted, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, add shredded cabbage mix, sour cream and 1/2 the spring onion to a large bowl. Toss to combine. Season to taste.
• Divide fries between plates. Top with American pulled beef and sour cream slaw.
• Top with a cheesy crisp and remaining spring onion to serve.